.TH DESKTOPMGR "1" "December 2025" "desktopmgr 202511250734-git" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
desktopmgr \- Desktop ManaGeR for installing and managing Linux desktop environments
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B desktopmgr
[\fI\,OPTIONS\/\fR] [\fI\,COMMAND\/\fR] [\fI\,ARGUMENTS\/\fR...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B desktopmgr
is a comprehensive desktop environment management tool for installing, updating, and managing various Linux desktop environments and window managers. It provides a unified interface for managing desktop configurations from window managers like i3, bspwm, dwm to full desktop environments like XFCE, KDE Plasma, and MATE.
.PP
desktopmgr supports installation from preconfigured GitHub repositories, automatic updates via cron, and provides search functionality to discover available desktop configurations. The tool also includes QEMU integration for launching virtual machines running Linux, Windows, macOS, and ARM-based systems.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B available
List all available desktop environment packages from the GitHub repository
.TP
.B list
List currently installed desktop environment packages
.TP
.B search \fI\,<term>\/\fR
Search for available desktop environment packages matching the specified term
.TP
.B install \fI\,<package>\/\fR
Install a desktop environment package from the preconfigured repository
.TP
.B update \fI\,[package]\/\fR
Update desktop environment packages. If no package is specified, updates all installed packages
.TP
.B download \fI\,<package>\/\fR
Download or clone a desktop environment configuration repository without installing
.TP
.B remove \fI\,<package>\/\fR
Remove an installed desktop environment package and its configuration files
.TP
.B cron \fI\,[package]\/\fR
Manage automatic desktop environment updates via cron job. Can be used to add, remove, or run cron-based updates
.TP
.B version \fI\,<package>\/\fR
Display version information for an installed desktop environment package
.TP
.B qemu \fI\,[linux|windows|macos|arm]\/\fR
Launch a QEMU virtual machine. Supports Linux (AlmaLinux), Windows, macOS (Ventura), and ARM64 (Alpine) systems. Each VM is launched in a Docker container with web-based management interface
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-help
Display help message and exit
.TP
.BR \-\-config
Generate or regenerate user configuration file
.TP
.BR \-\-version
Show script version information and exit
.TP
.BR \-\-options
Display all available command-line options and installed packages
.TP
.BR \-\-debug
Enable debug mode with verbose output and command tracing
.TP
.BR \-\-raw
Disable colorized output (useful for piping or logging)
.TP
.BR \-f ", " \-\-force
Force installation or operations, bypassing safety checks
.TP
.BR \-a ", " \-\-all
Apply operations to all applicable packages (e.g., update all, remove all)
